om your post.&#10;As your son has a statement any changes that you want to make to his provision or school will need to be made via the SEN Dept and his statement changed accordingly. Have you had an? This will give you a chance to put forward your concerns and your suggestions for what should be in his statement. Try to get an much support as you can from the health professionals that are involved with your son. You need evidence to support the points you are making. ACE has a booklet calledthat will guide you through the process of preparing and dealing with the meeting. See the section on Interim Reviews. &#10;If you want to change the type of school named in your son's statement (mainstream to special) you will also need to have changes made to parts 2 and 3 of the statement. If following a review the LA do not agree you could appeal to SEND. If your son's needs have changed significantly it may be better to ask for &#10;Have a look at the ACE booklet called. See the section on naming a school.&#10;I also wondered if you had any support from your Parent Partnership Service with this? They should be able to support you by attending meetings with you and helping you prepare paperwork. You can find local contact details on the &#10;You mention that you removed your son from school and I can't see from the post if he is currently getting any education, which he must be. If he isn't please post again and we can advise further. &#10;Good luck with this.&#10;best wishes&#10;ACE"/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1766" language="en" documentId="4890" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="ACE" date="29-08-12 10:58" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://www.netmums.com/coffeehouse/advice-support-40/special-needs-disabilities-support-502/809172-fighting-keep-my-son-mainstream-school-all.html" topic="mainstreaming" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="4890" notes="" title="fighting to keep my